        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">James Nelson to Austin, November 6, 1824.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Alxa [Alexandria]</placeName> <date when="1824-11-06">6th Novr 1824</date></p>
<p><persName>Mr. S F Austin</persName></p>

<p>Dear Sir. Having been disappointed in Receiving the Money
that was due me in this Count[r]y. I have been compeld again to
Commence work at my old trade of <persName>Enjineer </persName>in order to raise money
to discharge the debts I owe in your Count[r]y&#8212; I have now a
situation on board the steam boat Natchitoches&#8212; and as soon as
I can raise sufficient quantity of money shall forward it to you in
order to settle my debts&#8212; In the mean time I must beg you to
see that my property etc is not molested-&#8212;as I shall certainly send
money&#8212;and be out myself early in the <date n="Spring-1825">spring</date></p>

<p><persName>James Nelson  </persName>  [Rubric]</p>

        </div1>
